message.content:
Below is one systematic way to “read off” the two structures in the Main Target Image and then match each piece (in its correct orientation) from the Block‐Dictionary image.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

■  Overall Count and Layers

 •  LEFT TOWER  
   – Total of 8 blocks arranged in 6 vertical layers:  
     1) Bottom layer: 1 horizontal yellow rectangular block  
     2) Next layer: 2 vertical orange cylinders, side by side  
     3) Next layer: 1 horizontal yellow rectangular block  
     4) Next layer: 2 vertical green rectangular blocks, side by side  
     5) Next layer: 1 horizontal yellow rectangular block  
     6) Top layer: 1 red triangular wedge (the “roof”)  

 •  RIGHT STRUCTURE  
   – Total of 4 blocks in 3 main “levels”:  
     1) Base: 2 orange triangular wedges (left and right)  
     2) Middle: 1 vertical orange cylinder standing between those wedges  
     3) Top: 1 red “U”‐shaped (arch) block  

■  Spatial Relationships

 • Left Tower  
   The three flat yellow blocks form horizontal “ring” layers at bottom, middle, and near top. Two orange cylinders stand between the bottom and middle yellow layers. Two tall green blocks stand between the middle and upper yellow layers. A red triangular wedge caps it off.  

 • Right Structure  
   Two orange triangular wedges flank the base; the vertical orange cylinder sits in the center, and the red arch block rests on top of that cylinder with its semicircular opening facing upward.  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING THE REQUIRED BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Below are the exact Block‐Dictionary indices (and colors/orientations) needed.  
Remember, these must be used as‐pictured (no further rotations).

A)  LEFT TOWER (8 blocks)

1) Yellow rectangular plank (index 6) – BOTTOM  
2) Orange cylinder, vertical (index 9)  
3) Orange cylinder, vertical (index 9)  
4) Yellow rectangular plank (index 6) – MIDDLE  
5) Green rectangular block, vertical (index 4)  
6) Green rectangular block, vertical (index 4)  
7) Yellow rectangular plank (index 6) – UPPER  
8) Red triangular wedge (index 11) – ROOF  

B)  RIGHT STRUCTURE (4 blocks)

1) Orange triangular wedge (index 13) – Left base  
2) Orange triangular wedge (index 14) – Right base  
3) Orange cylinder, vertical (index 9)  
4) Red “U”‐shaped arch (index 1)  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Here is one possible sequence in which you might place/move each block:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 6        (bottom yellow plank of left tower)
  Step2:  Move block with index 9        (first orange cylinder, left tower)
  Step3:  Move block with index 9        (second orange cylinder, left tower)
  Step4:  Move block with index 6        (middle yellow plank of left tower)
  Step5:  Move block with index 4        (first green vertical block)
  Step6:  Move block with index 4        (second green vertical block)
  Step7:  Move block with index 6        (upper yellow plank of left tower)
  Step8:  Move block with index 11       (red triangular “roof” on left tower)
  Step9:  Move block with index 13       (left orange wedge of right structure)
  Step10: Move block with index 14       (right orange wedge of right structure)
  Step11: Move block with index 9        (orange cylinder in center of right structure)
  Step12: Move block with index 1        (red arch block on top of cylinder)
}

These twelve moves place all the required pieces in their correct orientations to reproduce the two target assemblies exactly as shown.
